For odd primes $p$, we derived $f(p) \le p$ generally (except possibly for $p=2$, but here we look at odd $p$).
Combining these observations, $f(n) \le 4n$ appears to be the strict upper bound derived from the number theoretic constraints (Lifting The Exponent Lemma and valuations).

